==Wauja==
===Etymology===
From {{affix|wau|yamukunaun|t1=children|-tope|t2=all, every}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|wau|/ˌja.mu.kuˌnɐ̃ʊ.tɨˈpɛ/}}
===Noun===
{{head|wau|noun}}
# all the [[children]] {{gloss|all the children in the village}}
#: {{ux|wau|Yamukunaun aya autukene mapa! Atukutapai '''yamukunauntope'''. Iya tukene mapa. Hoona, ayiu! Pa, yamukunaun iya itsenu wi. Tika tika tika ...|"Children, let's collect [wild] honey!" She invited all the children [of the village to come along]. They were going to collect honey. "All right, let's go!" [they said]. Well, all the children went with [the woman and her husband]. [The patter of their running feet was heard on the path:] ''tika tika tika...''}}
